Class QuizMenu

java.lang.Object
java.awt.event.MouseAdapter
FBLAQuiz.QuizMenu
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.event.MouseListener, java.awt.event.MouseMotionListener, java.awt.event.MouseWheelListener, java.util.EventListener
public class QuizMenu
extends java.awt.event.MouseAdapter
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener

Quiz Menu Class

The Quiz Menu class creates the home screen for the program, along with implementing methods for the showing of previous score reports and the database's questions.
Author:
Varun Unnithan

    • showQuestions

      protected void showQuestions​(int questionType)
      Shows all of the questions in the database for a given question type
      Parameters:
      questionType - An integer representing the type of question to display. The integer should be between 1-5, inclusive, with 1 being multiple choice, 2 is multiple select, 3 is true or false, 4 is fill in the blank, and 5 is matching.

    • showPasswordPrompt

      protected void showPasswordPrompt​(java.lang.String message, boolean verifyPassword)
      Creates a dialog box to ask for the user to enter a password, either to verify the user or change the password
      Parameters:
      message - The message to display on the dialog box
      verifyPassword - If this is true, it will verify this password with the correct one from the database. If this is false, the dialog box will act to change the password.
